transcript.text: Do you struggle to keep track of your print orders?
Let us share a case study of our clients Adam and John.
How Adam achieved success while John struggled using on Print shop.
John is a commercial printer, Adam is a printer and also outsources to John many print orders.
Adam cut down its manpower needed by 90% to process orders while increasing his repeat business using the On Print Shop Print order management solution.
While John only focused on new customers and invested in online marketing, he continued managing his existing customers orders manually.
Graphic designing, phone calls, print orders, quote estimation, everything was done still traditionally, so all his key team members were busy with repetitive tasks.
John wasn't able to attain the desired results.
There was no track of new customers acquired, productivity improvement or the return on investment.
Where Adam divided his goals into two phases.
First, increasing repeat business.
Second, grow new sales.
Adam focused on implementing its first phase, which was to increase the repeat sales.

Adam created B to C&B to B storefronts to simplify the ordering and reordering process by offering world class pre and post purchase experience, improving the team's productivity and reducing costs and freeing key people to focus on growth.
Where 70% of the estimation for the standard products was done online.
Offering online quotes for custom products, online designer studio to make design changes and my account to easily reorder.
Adam focuses on automating order management to reduce his key people's time in day-to-day operations.

He centrally managed print orders which were through emails, sales reps, online and walk insurance, auto generated invoices, job tickets and shipping labels and order workflow for timely delivery while easy ordering and reordering for customer or internal staff.
Now Adam has complete control over his business with his day-to-day reports, customers buying reports and highest selling products details.
Now phase two of Adam's goal was to grow new business where people focused on new sales and expansion.
Define niche segmented to grow sales, adding new products and sales segments.
John realizes the same and 1st focus on offering consistent and high end service to existing customers and increase productivity by implementing print order management solution.
If you looking to grow print sales or struggling with existing web to print solutions, contact us for order management consultation at onprintshop COM.
